properties.headline: Wind Advisory issued February 3 at 8:52PM PST until February 4 at 3:00PM PST by NWS Los Angeles/Oxnard CA
properties.description:
* WHAT...North winds 15 to 25 mph becoming northeast winds 20 to
30 mph with gusts up to 50 mph.

* WHERE...Santa Clarita Valley.

* WHEN...From 9 PM this evening to 3 PM PST Tuesday.

* IMPACTS...Gusty winds will blow around unsecured objects and
make driving difficult, especially for high profile vehicles.
Tree limbs could be blown down and a few power outages may
result.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...The wind, in combination with low
temperatures, will result in wind chill readings near 20 degrees
in some areas.
properties.instruction:
Use extra caution when driving, especially if operating a high
profile vehicle. Secure outdoor objects.

NWSheadline: WIND ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 3 PM PST TUESDAY
